videos.description: Ole Miss takes the opening drive and goes right down the field, finishing with a three-yard slant pass to Damore'ea Stringfellow for the opening touchdown of the game.
videos.headline: Ole Miss strikes first with touchdown pass to Stringfellow

videos.description: Ole Miss starting cornerback Kendarius Webster gets injured while landing after a deep pass from Seminoles quarterback Deondre Francois.
videos.headline: Webster goes down for Ole Miss

videos.description: Ole Miss was rolling early until Derwin James jumps the route and picks off Chad Kelly to give Florida State a much-needed boost.
videos.headline: James ends Ole Miss' momentum with interception for Florida State

videos.description: Starting Rebel cornerback Kendarius Webster gets carted off with an apparent leg injury, but it doesn't stop him from shouting instructions to his team to pump them up.
videos.headline: Kendarius Webster carted off for Ole Miss with apparent leg injury

videos.description: Deondre Fancois hits Dalvin Cook on a wheel route for a 24-yard gain for Florida State.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Francois connects with Cook for 24 yards) 2016/09/05 ESHEET

videos.headline: Francois connects with Cook for 24 yards

videos.description: Chad Kelly pass complete to D.K. Metcalf who tips ball to himself for a 3 yd TD
videos.headline: D.K. Metcalf tips ball to himself in the end zone for a TD.

videos.description: Chad Kelly's pass is complete to Taz Zettergren for 37 yards and a Florida State first down.
videos.headline: Kelly picks up 37 yards with pass to Zettergren

videos.description: Ole Miss is firing on all cylinders as Chad Kelly finds Evan Engram on 3rd-and-17 open over the middle for his third touchdown pass to put the Rebels ahead 21-3.
videos.headline: Ole Miss rolling with Kelly's third TD pass

videos.description: Dalvin Cook catches the ball with all kinds of space to waltz into the end zone until he fumbles before crossing the goal line. Florida State would fail to punch it in and have to settle for a field goal.
videos.headline: Cook fumbles the ball to miss out on easy touchdown

videos.description: Akeem Judd takes the handoff and throws a nasty juke move that fakes out a Florida State defender before racing into the end zone to increase Ole Miss' lead to 28-6.
videos.headline: Judd's sweet juke move increases Ole Miss' lead

videos.description: Florida State finally finds the end zone when Deondre Francois hangs in the pocket just long enough to find Travis Rudolph over the middle for the touchdown to cut the Ole Miss lead to 28-13.
videos.headline: Francois gets crushed but still connects for TD pass

videos.description: Chad Kelly's pass goes off Evan Engram's hands to Marcus Lewis, who makes the diving interception to give Florida State back the ball in Ole Miss territory.
videos.headline: Lewis makes the interception to spark Florida State

videos.description: Ole Miss blows up the play, but Deondre Francois shows off his athleticism by bouncing to the outside and turning on the jets before being dragged down at the goal line. Florida State would punch it in to cut the score to 28-23.
videos.headline: Francois shows off athleticism to get Seminoles to the goal line

videos.description: Freddie Stevenson run for 1 yd for a TD
videos.headline: Freddie Stevenson pounds the ball in for the TD

videos.description: Florida State makes it two forced turnovers in the last three Ole Miss snaps when  DeMarcus Walker sacks Chad Kelly and has him cough up the ball to get the Seminoles in scoring position again.
videos.headline: Florida State sacks Kelly to force another turnover

videos.description: After a disastrous first half, Florida State is flying in the third quarter when Kermit Whitfield finds the end zone to give the Seminoles their first lead of the game at 29-28.
videos.headline: Whitfield's touchdown put Florida State ahead for the first time

videos.description: Bobo Wilson tries to field a punt off the bounce, but gets hit and fumbles, fortunately, into the arms of a teammate.
videos.headline: Seminoles fortunate after Wilson blunder

videos.description: Deondre Francois has Florida State rolling, finding Ryan Izzo wide-open on the play-action pass that gets the Seminoles to the goal line. Florida State would punch it in two plays later to make it 36-28.
videos.headline: Francois' play action gets FSU to the goal line

videos.description: Florida State continues its furious third quarter when Deondre Francois finds Ryan Izzo in the back of the end zone to increase the Seminoles lead to 36-28.
videos.headline: Francois finds Izzo for another Florida State touchdown

videos.description: Florida State kicker Ricky Aguayo, younger brother of former Seminole kicker Roberto Aguayo, makes a 40-yard field goal and shows his teammates he has ice in his veins.
videos.headline: Ricky Aguayo shows he has ice in his veins

videos.description: Ole Miss goes down the field in four plays, capped off with Chad Kelly's touch pass to Van Jefferson in the end zone, which cuts Florida State's lead to 39-34.
videos.headline: Ole Miss strikes back with Kelly's fourth TD pass

videos.description: Florida State's Kermit Whitfield takes the kickoff return to the FSU 47 after a couple of impressive cuts.
videos.headline: Kermit Whitfield explodes for long return

videos.description: Deondre Francois' pass is complete to Travis Rudolph for 27 yards and a Florida State first down.
videos.headline: Francois' pass to Rudolph keeps the drive alive

videos.description: Florida State freshman kicker Ricky Aguayo hits a 44-yard field goal to extend his team's lead to 42-34.
videos.headline: Aguayo now 5-for-5 in collegiate debut

videos.description: Ricky Aguayo notches his sixth field goal of the game despite a slight deflection to give FSU a 45-34 lead.
videos.headline: Aguayo breaks school record for made FG attempts in single game

videos.description: Facing fourth down, Damore'ea Stringfellow makes an incredible catch on the sidelines to keep Ole Miss alive.
videos.headline: Stringfellow makes remarkable catch to keep Ole Miss alive

videos.description: With Ole Miss driving, Chad Kelly goes deep down the sidelines but Tarvarus McFadden makes the interception to finish off Ole Miss' chances.
videos.headline: McFadden picks off Kelly to end late Ole Miss drive

videos.description: Kirk Herbstreit joins SVP to break down No. 4 Florida State's 45-34 victory over No. 11 Ole Miss, including what FSU quarterback Deondre Francois showed in the victory.

videos.headline: How was FSU able to turn it around in the second half?
